<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,283,669]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,320,346]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Pujade-Villar, J. &amp; Wang, Y. &amp; Guo, R. &amp; Chen, X." box="[322,632,319,346]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="417 - 423" refId="ref51457" refString="Pujade-Villar, J., Wang, Y., Guo, R. &amp; Chen, X. (2014 d) New species of gallwasps inducing in Quercus fabri and its inquiline (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae) in China. Zoological Systematics, 39 (3), 417 - 423. https: // doi. org / 10.11865 / zs 20140308" type="journal article" year="2014">
Pujade-Villar 
<emphasis box="[479,529,319,345]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">et al</emphasis>
. (2014d)
</bibRefCitation>
state that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pujade-Villar, Wang, Guo &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2014" box="[747,840,319,346]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Saphonecrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fabris">
<emphasis box="[747,840,319,346]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">S. fabris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was reared from galls of 
<taxonomicName box="[1129,1305,319,345]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Andricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavus">
<emphasis box="[1129,1305,319,345]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Andricus flavus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on 
<taxonomicName box="[1347,1436,319,346]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fabri">
<emphasis box="[1347,1436,319,346]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Q. fabri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(sect. 
<taxonomicName box="[218,312,356,382]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[218,312,356,382]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Quercus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The gall inducer adults presumed to have emerged from these galls were confirmed to be 
<taxonomicName authority="(Kieffer, 1906)" authorityName="Melika &amp; Abrahamson" authorityYear="2002" baseAuthorityName="Kieffer" baseAuthorityYear="1906" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Andricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mairei">
<emphasis box="[1333,1436,356,382]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">A. mairei</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kieffer, J. J." box="[158,311,391,417]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="101 - 110" refId="ref45698" refString="Kieffer, J. J. (1906) Description d'un genre nouveau et deux especes nouvelles. Marcellia, 5, 101 - 110." type="journal article" year="1906">Kieffer, 1906</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName box="[360,458,391,418]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Andricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavus">
<emphasis box="[360,458,391,418]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">A. flavus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). However, the galls mentioned in 
<bibRefCitation author="Pujade-Villar, J. &amp; Wang, Y. &amp; Guo, R. &amp; Chen, X." box="[855,1165,391,418]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="417 - 423" refId="ref51457" refString="Pujade-Villar, J., Wang, Y., Guo, R. &amp; Chen, X. (2014 d) New species of gallwasps inducing in Quercus fabri and its inquiline (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae) in China. Zoological Systematics, 39 (3), 417 - 423. https: // doi. org / 10.11865 / zs 20140308" type="journal article" year="2014">
Pujade-Villar 
<emphasis box="[1012,1062,391,417]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">et al</emphasis>
. (2014d)
</bibRefCitation>
do not correspond to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Melika &amp; Abrahamson" authorityYear="2002" baseAuthorityName="Kieffer" baseAuthorityYear="1906" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Andricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mairei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">A. mairei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but to an undetermined gall wasp (
<bibRefCitation author="Pujade-Villar, J. &amp; Wang, Y. &amp; Guo, R. &amp; Cuesta-Porta, V. &amp; Arnedo, M. A. &amp; Melika, G." box="[619,911,427,454]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="507 - 525" refId="ref51522" refString="Pujade-Villar, J., Wang, Y., Guo, R., Cuesta-Porta, V., Arnedo, M. A. &amp; Melika, G. (2020 c) Current status of Andricus mairei (Kieffer), with synonymization of two species from China (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae). Zootaxa, 4808 (3), 507 - 525. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4808.3.6" type="journal article" year="2020">
Pujade-Villar 
<emphasis box="[776,825,427,453]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">et al</emphasis>
. 2020c
</bibRefCitation>
). Furthermore, the host plant of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Melika &amp; Abrahamson" authorityYear="2002" baseAuthorityName="Kieffer" baseAuthorityYear="1906" box="[1267,1369,428,454]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Andricus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mairei">
<emphasis box="[1267,1369,428,454]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">A. mairei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not 
<taxonomicName box="[151,240,463,490]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fabri">
<emphasis box="[151,240,463,490]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Q. fabri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but 
<taxonomicName authority="(Pujade-Villar et al. 2020 c)" baseAuthorityName="Pujade-Villar" baseAuthorityYear="2020" box="[298,732,463,490]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="serrata">
<emphasis box="[298,414,464,490]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Q. serrata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Pujade-Villar, J. &amp; Wang, Y. &amp; Guo, R. &amp; Cuesta-Porta, V. &amp; Arnedo, M. A. &amp; Melika, G." box="[428,724,463,490]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="507 - 525" refId="ref51522" refString="Pujade-Villar, J., Wang, Y., Guo, R., Cuesta-Porta, V., Arnedo, M. A. &amp; Melika, G. (2020 c) Current status of Andricus mairei (Kieffer), with synonymization of two species from China (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae). Zootaxa, 4808 (3), 507 - 525. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4808.3.6" type="journal article" year="2020">
Pujade-Villar 
<emphasis box="[587,637,463,489]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">et al</emphasis>
. 2020c
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. According to the new material examined in 
<bibRefCitation author="Lobato-Vila, I. &amp; Wang, Y. &amp; Melika, G. &amp; Guo, R. &amp; Xiaoxue, J. &amp; Pujade-Villar, J." pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="1 - 28" refId="ref46786" refString="Lobato-Vila, I., Wang, Y., Melika, G., Guo, R., Xiaoxue, J. &amp; Pujade-Villar, J. (2021 b) A taxonomic review of the gall wasp genus Saphonecrus Dalla-Torre &amp; Kieffer and other oak cynipid inquilines (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae) from mainland China, with updated keys to Eastern Palaearctic and Oriental species. Zoological Studies, 60 (10), 1 - 28. https: // doi. org / 10.6620 / ZS. 2021.60 - 10" type="journal article" year="2021">
Lobato-Vila 
<emphasis box="[1380,1429,463,489]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">et al</emphasis>
. (2021b)
</bibRefCitation>
and to the determination conflict addressed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Pujade-Villar, J. &amp; Wang, Y. &amp; Guo, R. &amp; Cuesta-Porta, V. &amp; Arnedo, M. A. &amp; Melika, G." box="[768,1076,499,526]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="507 - 525" refId="ref51522" refString="Pujade-Villar, J., Wang, Y., Guo, R., Cuesta-Porta, V., Arnedo, M. A. &amp; Melika, G. (2020 c) Current status of Andricus mairei (Kieffer), with synonymization of two species from China (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae). Zootaxa, 4808 (3), 507 - 525. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4808.3.6" type="journal article" year="2020">
Pujade-Villar 
<emphasis box="[924,973,499,525]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">et al</emphasis>
. (2020c)
</bibRefCitation>
, the biology of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pujade-Villar, Wang, Guo &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2014" box="[1249,1342,499,526]" class="Insecta" family="Cynipidae" genus="Saphonecrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fabris">
<emphasis box="[1249,1342,499,526]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">S. fabris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(at least of its 
<typeStatus box="[215,263,536,562]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">type</typeStatus>
material) remains uncertain.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="35" pageNumber="36" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="35.[151,1437,283,669]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,295,571,597]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Biology.</emphasis>
Uncertain. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Lobato-Vila, I. &amp; Wang, Y. &amp; Melika, G. &amp; Guo, R. &amp; Xiaoxue, J. &amp; Pujade-Villar, J." box="[585,887,571,598]" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" pagination="1 - 28" refId="ref46786" refString="Lobato-Vila, I., Wang, Y., Melika, G., Guo, R., Xiaoxue, J. &amp; Pujade-Villar, J. (2021 b) A taxonomic review of the gall wasp genus Saphonecrus Dalla-Torre &amp; Kieffer and other oak cynipid inquilines (Hymenoptera: Cynipidae) from mainland China, with updated keys to Eastern Palaearctic and Oriental species. Zoological Studies, 60 (10), 1 - 28. https: // doi. org / 10.6620 / ZS. 2021.60 - 10" type="journal article" year="2021">
Lobato-Vila 
<emphasis box="[729,780,571,597]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">et al</emphasis>
. (2021b)
</bibRefCitation>
, reared from galls on the midrib of leaves of 
<taxonomicName authority="A. Camus" authorityName="A. Camus" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="stewardiana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Q. stewardiana</emphasis>
A. Camus
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Huang &amp; Chang" authorityName="Huang &amp; Chang" box="[462,765,607,634]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Quercus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ciliaris">
<emphasis box="[462,575,607,634]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Q. ciliaris</emphasis>
Huang &amp; Chang
</taxonomicName>
(sect. 
<taxonomicName box="[839,1026,607,633]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Cyclobalanopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="35" pageNumber="36" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[839,1026,607,633]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="36">Cyclobalanopsis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The gall inducer has yet to be confirmed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
